results.name: Sum of the n-th antidiagonal of infinite Sudoku-type array A269526.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2000
example: For n = 6 the sum of all elements of the 6th antidiagonal of the square array A269526 is 6 + 7 + 3 + 2 + 8 + 5 = 31, so a(6) = 31.
